                values('Aphrodes bicincta','','General color light brown to dark brown. Crown with dark triangular markings on either side of middle, basal half light cream in male; pronotum light cream; elytra light brown to dark brown, Veins white to cream; female uniformly light tan to light brown.(Nielson, 1968)','Aphrodes','Medium size, robust species.male 5.40—5.90 mm., female 6.80—7.30 mm. (Nielson, 1968)','Cicadellidae','This species, related to albifrons, can be distinguished by the aedeagus with the distal pair of spines near the middle of the shaft and serrate margins on the distal end of the shaft.(Nielson 1968)');
            
