                values('Agalliana sticticollis','http://insectvectors.science/files/specimens/i14075.jpg','General color light brown or tan with black markings on crown, pronotum, and elytra; crown tan to light brown with two black spots on anterior margin, black markings near inner margin of eye in males; pronotum tan with numerous black specks and dark markings scattered on surface especially in males; elytra light brown to gray, veins light brown to dark brown; cornmissure with dark brown or black stripes between claval veins, claval veins along commissure white or ivory.(Nielson, 1968)','Agalliana','Small, somewhat linear species. male 3.00—3.50 mm., female 2.90—3.30 mm. (Nielson, 1968)','Cicadellidae','This species, related to ensigera, can be separated easily by the bifurcate spine on the 10th segment.(Nielson 1968)');
            
