i&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>wings when viewed from above (as opposed to the more convex outline of P. spumarius) and their overall pattern of markings. They are much smaller than Aphrophora species.The taxonomic status of Neophilaenus longiceps as a separate species from N. lineatus is uncertain; it may be simply a&nbsp; style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>saltmarsh race of N. lineatus. Its appearance is very similar&nbsp; style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>but it can be distinguished by the dimensions of the central&nbsp; style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>`plate` on the top of the head (wider than long in N. longiceps&nbsp; style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>compared to longer than wide in N. lineatus). N. longiceps is&nbsp; style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>also slightly larger. style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;; font-size: 1rem;'>(Harkin &amp; Stewart 2019)','Neophilaenus','Adults are typically 6 – 7mm long; females are somewhat  larger than males.','Aphrophoridae','');
            
                insert into insecte(nom,image_url,description_insecte,partie1,partie2,famille,diagnostic)
                values('Anoterostemma ivanhofi','http://insectvectors.science/files/vectors/2021/06/Ano-sp.jpeg','A. ivanhofi has a squat body outline, adults being only 2.5—&nbsp; 4.5mm long.As with all leafhoppers, the hind tibiae have&nbsp;rows of spines running along their entire length.A. ivanhofi are brachypterous i.e. they have very shortened&nbsp;forewings, and hindwings that are reduced in size or completely absent. The abdomen is entirely black apart from the&nbsp;terminal segments; the background colour of the head, thorax and wings is light brown with distinctive dark brown/black&nbsp;markings.&nbsp;(Harkin &amp; Stewart 2019)','Anoterostemma','','Cicadellidae','');
            
